719408f-b.title: Manhattan: Dyer Avenue - 34th Street (West)
719408f-b.text:
Dyer Ave., north from West 34th to 42nd (background) Streets.
This thoroughfare,recently constructed in the center of the blocks
between Ninth and Tenth Aves., is actually the entrance through to t
new Lincoln Tunnel. No. 2 is similar from West 35th Street; the
Tunnel mouth being at the base of the incline.
February 10, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.
